(text "TPS26630 accepts 7-22V nominal; 0.1% ladder targets 5.53V/22.99V rising UV/OV and a 3A limit." (at 379.73 25.4 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 363bc1a6-5855-50a4-8450-784b24d1da69))
(text "U15 validates USB near 15V and AUX across 7-22V, gives USB priority, and prevents inactive-source backfeed." (at 379.73 31.75 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid aee725d4-8321-5336-b188-f652580eba5f))
(text "SMCJ24CA protects the 67V eFuse input; active OVP protects the BQ25798 24V recommended input limit." (at 379.73 38.1 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 53b6b2d4-4dc9-5e96-b7fb-66fb229a0e00))
(text "NOTE: no wires used - connectivity is via matching label names (valid KiCad practice)." (at 20.32 219.71 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 53e262ee-6f18-55d7-9da9-1fdd66988ddc))
(text "J2: pins 1/2 PACK+, pins 3/4 PACK-, pin 5 cell1 tap, pin 6 cell2 tap. Verify harness order before first connection." (at 20.32 226.06 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 84a5b0d8-a894-5118-acb7-33972f9c253f))
(text "U719 BQ7791500 autonomously protects each cell at 4.20V OV / 2.90V UV and drives back-to-back low-side FETs." (at 20.32 232.41 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid b4d1618f-7b7f-57ab-83c7-8bfb73f43b23))
(text "RS11=8mOhm gives 7.5A nominal OCD and 15A nominal SCD; U11/RS10 and F1 remain independent tighter/secondary protection." (at 20.32 237.49 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 3663f882-3329-5ed9-b8a0-081632f4d2d3))
(text "No motherboard battery thermistors are fitted. U719 TS uses TI's 10k-to-VSS unused-function connection; VTB is NC." (at 20.32 243.84 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid cc55da9e-c8fe-5ccc-8c30-314dd0d48b44))
(text "BQ25798 /CE is fail-off: REGN pulls it high; active-high CHG_ENABLE turns Q700 on only after EC source validation." (at 20.32 250.19 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 13f6e1f1-2910-5f24-a11b-f4afb40e6673))
(text "U2 ILIM_HIZ divider is a 3.0A hardware ceiling; EC programs a lower IINDPM from the selected TPS25751A Active PDO Contract (0x31)." (at 20.32 256.54 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid f21564c0-a551-579e-9d22-5950d9dc372a))
(text "J190 is the one 7-22V nominal AUX/solar input; TPS26630 protects it before BQ25798." (at 20.32 264.16 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 51212ce9-85fe-5def-a313-3d453f8ab492))
(text "Solar MPPT is implemented by BQ25798 firmware on this same input; there is no second charger path." (at 20.32 271.78 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid b8044c0e-cf7a-5d5d-8390-c883a9c8b63b))
(text "AUX_DC_ADC measures the post-reverse-FET input so firmware can detect droop and reduce BQ25798 input current." (at 20.32 287.02 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 04ee52a1-7095-5e58-a101-9355f7e7f46c))
(text "U2 VAC1/VAC2 tie to VBUS_COMBINED in no-external-mux mode; ACDRV1/2 go to GND." (at 20.32 294.64 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 2ba4bd7c-36f1-54f5-b1fe-630ff6d90cd2))
(text "Q25 follows BQ25798EVM-842: SDRV disconnects pack discharge for electronic ship/hard-off while adapter charging can wake the pack." (at 20.32 302.26 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 96336d88-1b61-56d8-a5da-3c82257979e7))
(text "U11 accepts about 8.45-13.57V nominal; 11mOhm RS10 gives 4.55A nominal and <=5.51A worst-case trips." (at 20.32 309.88 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 0465a2c2-7401-5309-bbd1-0b89be29779e))
(text "BQ25798 TS is fixed at 58.9% REGN by 5.24k/7.50k; firmware sets TS_IGNORE=1. BQ34Z100 TS has 10k to VSS; set TEMPS=0." (at 20.32 317.5 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 6ed72109-69cf-5916-a7a2-af20f29893a8))
(text "MANDATORY STARTUP: hold MU_12V_ENABLE low; read TPS25751A PD Status 0x35 plus Active PDO/RDO 0x31/0x32; program VSYSMIN and IINDPM <= min(PDO-0.25A, 2.75A); require VSYS >=10.0V." (at 20.32 325.12 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid f1cd8f94-109c-5106-9290-df41f702b833))
(text "Then assert MU_12V_ENABLE and require MU_12V_PG within 20ms. Any PG timeout, source-invalid, charger fault, watchdog fault, or VSYS<10V disables the Mu rail." (at 20.32 332.74 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid c933fb36-fa1d-5e10-b206-1deea656b0e0))
(text "BQ25798 firmware must set STOP_WD_CHG=1 and TS_IGNORE=1, service faults, validate PDO current, and assert CHG_ENABLE only after safe limits are programmed." (at 20.32 340.36 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 5b74542e-39da-5e9c-b76b-1a8f433b7459))
(text "U718 is the aggregate AON safety boundary: 1.51A typical limit, true reverse blocking, 6.20V nominal UVLO, and 22.40V nominal OVLO." (at 20.32 347.98 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 4b344e1f-7c75-533a-9025-8cbf23f06efd))
(text "AON UVLO corners are 6.06-6.36V: default 5V USB-C is negotiation-only; TPS25751A dead-battery boot must obtain a valid higher-voltage PDO before EC_AON_IN starts." (at 20.32 355.6 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 48796e0a-d850-5417-864e-fdca2efce441))
(text "A 5V-only USB-C source leaves the laptop off. AON_FAULT_N inhibits charging and Mu start; the service connector remains the assembly hard disconnect." (at 20.32 363.22 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 1dcdaabc-4c0e-5e1e-b96c-44ba84c2e406))
(text "C746 provides low-ESR hold-up through LTC4418 break-before-make source switching." (at 20.32 370.84 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27))) (uuid 8ae99781-7322-5345-963d-c3e33c644c40))
